<br>
The best way to make TLC work IMO is, instead of making trivial items not drop at all, make them NO DROP. Any non trivial items are droppable as they are now.<br>
<br>
This means - <br>
Farming trivial stuff is impossible, as you can not sell it or give it away.<br>
If you miss out on a quest item, or a useful newb item, you can still get it and use it yourself.<br>
<br>
This way combines the benefits of both systems. The main problem is probably in the coding. I doubt we will see this happen as it is not the simple programming change that TLC is (ie somehow items would have to &quot;remember if they are NO DROP or not) <p><center><img src="http://members.aol.com/jimturner99/gyrhawk"></center> <b><center>Gyrhawk - Tunare's Falconer</center></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uquillionthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quillion the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/29/01 10:09:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: That is correct, Ichi</span><hr size=1> Ya know falconer, <br>
